column5: There was some discussion on a rendition of the U.S. anthem. I thought the Canada forum should have a similar distraction. I offer for your listening pleasure an interesting interpretation of Canada's national anthem.......http://www.nfb.ca/film/william_shatner_sings_o_canada/ *my apologies to the folk from Wisconsin, who likely didn't realize Canada was a different country and had it's own anthem.
Being in WI only can say OUCH! Roy

Now, Gord . . . . . you keep taking those cracks at Cheeseheads and you'll not get your smoked aged Wisconsin cheddar next week . . . maybe we won't introduce you to genuine Pennsylvania Dutch recipe pickled eggs either!
Jay, as you know, Wisconsinites have the best sense of humor....hence my selection. Now, if I had picked on those Illinois friendly folk, it would have gone totally over their heads.....
James T actually did an album. Did a cover of E. Johns "Rocket Man."
